[Student "S"]
{NORTH realizes SOUTH has fewer than 8 points, but the 3\S support bid is enough 
for her to try a RKCB 4NT bid.

SOUTH shows two Key Cards and NORTH figures they will be the \SK and one of the 
red Aces. So she bids 6\S. If instead the Key Cards are the two red Aces NORTH 
might possibly make all thirteen tricks with a finesse.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "3"]
[Dealer "E"]
[Vulnerable "EW"]
